entries.title: Oil Rises in Likely Bargain Hunting
entries.description: Oil rose in early Asian trade, rebounding from losses earlier in the week.

entries.title: Most Asian Currencies Strengthen Slightly on Fed Rate-Cut Hopes
entries.description: Most Asian currencies strengthened slightly against USD in the early morning session on hopes for Fed rate cuts which would bolster appetite for risky assets.

entries.title: JGBs Edge Higher, Aided by Gains in Treasurys
entries.description: JGBs edged higher in the morning Tokyo session, tracking overnight gains in Treasurys.

entries.title: Gold Steady, Underpinned by Fed Rate-Cut Prospects
entries.description: Gold was steady in the early morning Asian session, underpinned by prospects for Fed rate cuts driven by U.S. data released overnight.

entries.title: Two Biden administration officials were in the Middle East to revive stalled talks on a deal that would impose a cease-fire in the war in Gaza and free hostages held by Hamas.
entries.description: Two Biden administration officials were in the Middle East to revive stalled talks on a deal that would impose a cease-fire in the war in Gaza and free hostages held by Hamas.

entries.title: Psychiatrist Henry Jarecki said he had a consensual relationship with a woman who filed a lawsuit accusing him of sexual assault after she was sent to him for treatment by Jeffrey Epstein.

entries.title: New York state will delay indefinitely a proposed June 30 start date for auto congestion pricing in Manhattan south of 60th Street, Gov. Kathy Hochul said.
entries.description: New York state will delay indefinitely a proposed June 30 start date for auto congestion pricing in Manhattan south of 60th Street, Gov. Kathy Hochul said.

entries.title: More than a dozen people were arrested at Stanford University after pro-Palestinian protesters barricaded themselves in the president's office.

entries.title: Hunter Biden's ex-wife and an ex-girlfriend took the stand in his trial as prosecutors tried to persuade jurors that he lied about his drug use during a 2018 firearm purchase.

entries.title: Putin said any deal to free Wall Street Journal reporter Evan Gershkovich would come only through a mutually beneficial agreement with the U.S.

entries.title: Senate Republicans blocked a Democratic measure that would protect access to contraception nationwide, in a vote designed to show the contrast between the two parties on women's reproductive choices headed into the fall election.

entries.title: The United Nations atomic agency, in a move led by European governments, formally rebuked Iran over advances in its nuclear program and failure to cooperate with the body.

entries.title: The Bank of Canada cut its main interest rate by a quarter percentage point, becoming the first G-7 central bank to provide rate relief after a period of global policy tightening.

entries.title: A federal court in New Orleans struck down rules the SEC issued that would have governed the terms private-equity and hedge-fund firms set with their investors.

entries.title: Discount retailer Dollar Tree said it was exploring a potential sale or spinoff of Family Dollar, which has struggled to lift sales.

entries.title: A European Union court ruling deprived McDonald's of its exclusive right to call chicken sandwiches sold in the bloc a "Big Mac."
entries.description: A European Union court ruling deprived McDonald’s of its exclusive right to call chicken sandwiches sold in the bloc a “Big Mac.”

entries.title: Zara owner Inditex made a positive start to its second quarter with sales growth buoyed by the success of its spring/summer collections.

entries.title: U.S. households are reaping investment income at record levels, allowing them to spend more on outlays that potentially make the Fed's inflation target harder to reach.
